Ahmed Usham is the incumbent [[Attorney General of the Maldives|Attorney General]] of the [[Maldives]]. Earlier, he served as Deputy Solicitor General at the Attorney General’s Office, and as Deputy Attorney General. He currently serving as the [[Maldives National Party|Maldives National Party's]] deputy leader.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Nov 17 |first=0 |last2=2023 19:31 |title=Dr. Muizzu’s promising cabinet |url=https://en.sun.mv/85974 |access-date=2023-11-18 |website=SunOnline International |language=en}}</ref>

Ahmed Usham is the incumbent [[Attorney General of the Maldives|Attorney General]] of the [[Maldives]]. Earlier, he served as Deputy Solicitor General at the Attorney General’s Office, and as Deputy Attorney General. He currently serving as the [[Maldives National Party|Maldives National Party's]] deputy leader.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Nov 17 |first=0 |last2=2023 19:31 |title=Dr. Muizzu’s promising cabinet |url=https://en.sun.mv/85974 |access-date=2023-11-18 |website=SunOnline International |language=en}}</ref>
